<P>
   (NYT15) HAMPSHIRE HILLS, N.H. -- Jan. 30. 2000 -- BUSH-DYNASTY
-- Former President George Bush, Gov. George W. Bush of Texas,
left, joined by the family matriarch, Barbara Bush far right, and
three of George W.'s four siblings, campaign for votes in the New
Hampshire primary, Saturday. Three days before the nation's first
primary in New Hampshire and with some polls showing Bush closing
on Arizona Sen. John McCain, the Texan looked and acted like a
winner as he and his extended family took the stage before almost
2,000 chanting, foot-stomping, placard-waving supporters. (Stephen
Crowley/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) PETERBOROUGH, N.H. -- Jan. 30, 2000 -- NH-CAMPAIGN-RDP-9
