Republican Presidential Candidate Steve Forbes shakes hands with a
supporter after a ``Statewide Road to Victory Rally'' in Nashua,
Sunday. Running a distant third in Republican polling here,
millionaire publisher Forbes kept his eye on George W. Bush. After
the Texan told ``Fox News Sunday'' that he would cut taxes
``hopefully in the first term,'' Forbes questioned Bush's
commitment to the issue. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) SOMERSWORTH, N.H. -- Jan. 30, 2000 -- NH-CAMPAIGN-RDP-6
