their team's 23-16 victory over the Tennessee Titans in Super Bowl
XXXIV, Sunday. Warner, with just 1 minute 54 seconds left in the
game, connected on a 73-yard deep pass, one that will surely go
down as one of the most spectacular in championship history, and
broke a 16-16 tie which clinched the victory for the Rams. (Barton
Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
