<P>
   (NYT31) ATLANTA -- Jan. 30, 2000 -- FBN-SUPER-BOWL-9 -- The
Tennessee Titans Kevin Dyson reaches but is unable to put the ball
in the end zone against the St. Louis Rams on the last second play
of Super Bowl XXXIV, Sunday. Rams quarterback Kurt Warner, with
just 1 minute 54 seconds left in the game, connected on a 73-yard
deep pass, one that will surely go down as one of the most
spectacular in championship history, and broke a 16-16 tie and made
the Rams 23-16 winners over Tennessee in Super Bowl XXXIV, Sunday.
(Michelle V. Agins/The New York Times)
