Rams quarterback Kurt Warner, with just 1 minute 54 seconds left in
the game, connected on a 73-yard deep pass, one that will surely go
down as one of the most spectacular in championship history, and
broke a 16-16 tie and made the Rams 23-16 winners over Tennessee in
Super Bowl XXXIV, Sunday. (Michelle V. Agins/The New York Times)
